pick up the other call.

757
01:11:08,470 --> 01:11:10,430
Great.

758
01:11:21,990 --> 01:11:25,740
Look, let'sjust be honest here.
We're just at the beginning...

759
01:11:25,870 --> 01:11:28,870
and I don't expect
you or I to change...

760
01:11:28,950 --> 01:11:31,410
the course of where
our lives were headed...

761
01:11:31,500 --> 01:11:33,790
because of one date.

762
01:11:33,870 --> 01:11:38,340
And if you do go to New York,
we can develop this.

763
01:11:38,420 --> 01:11:41,590
We'll just be forced to take it slow.

764
01:11:41,670 --> 01:11:45,430
And in the end, I think
that's defiinitely better.

765
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:50,260
I mean, this is our second time around,
David. I didn't expect us...

766
01:11:50,350 --> 01:11:52,640
to get carried away.

767
01:11:54,890 --> 01:11:58,730
But I guess "congratulations"
is the right thing to say.

768
01:12:23,550 --> 01:12:25,760
David, it's Elijah.

769
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:27,840
It was so obvious.

770
01:12:27,970 --> 01:12:30,260
It was this one issue
that brought it back for me--

771
01:12:30,390 --> 01:12:32,350
Century Comics 117.

772
01:12:32,470 --> 01:12:34,600
That's where this group,
the Coalition of Evil...

773
01:12:34,680 --> 01:12:37,140
tried to ascertain the weakness
of every superhero...

774
01:12:37,270 --> 01:12:40,690
because they all have one,
just like you.

775
01:12:40,770 --> 01:12:44,820
Your bones don't break.
Mine do. That's clear.

776
01:12:44,900 --> 01:12:48,320
Your cells react to bacteria
and viruses differently than mine.

777
01:12:48,450 --> 01:12:52,370
You don't get sick.
I do. That's also clear.

778
01:12:52,490 --> 01:12:57,790
But for some reason, you and I
react the exact same way to water.

779
01:12:57,870 --> 01:13:00,250
We swallow it too fast, we choke.

780
01:13:00,380 --> 01:13:02,590
We get some in our lungs, we drown.

781
01:13:02,710 --> 01:13:07,760
However unreal it may seem,
we are connected, you and I.

782
01:13:07,880 --> 01:13:12,510
We're on the same curve,
just on opposite ends.

783
01:13:12,640 --> 01:13:16,680
The point of all this is we
now know something we didn't.

784
01:13:16,770 --> 01:13:20,270
You have a weakness-- water.

785
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:23,320
It's like your kryptonite.

786
01:13:23,440 --> 01:13:25,740
You hearing me, David?

787
01:15:40,700 --> 01:15:42,660
Audrey?

788
01:16:16,110 --> 01:16:18,490
Gotcha. Come on.

789
01:16:36,130 --> 01:16:38,970
Audrey. Audrey.

790
01:16:44,850 --> 01:16:46,810
Hey!

791
01:16:50,940 --> 01:16:53,780
You'll be okay.

792
01:16:53,900 --> 01:16:57,660
What-- What happened?

793
01:16:57,780 --> 01:17:01,700
I thought I was--
I thought I was dead.

794
01:17:01,780 --> 01:17:03,740
Me too.

795
01:17:08,250 --> 01:17:10,210
Is she all right?

796
01:17:10,330 --> 01:17:12,630
I think her leg's broken.

797
01:17:12,750 --> 01:17:15,300
Are you hurt?

798
01:17:15,380 --> 01:17:17,590
Hey, man, are you hurt?

799
01:17:48,040 --> 01:17:50,000
Hello.

800
01:17:50,120 --> 01:17:52,880
I wasn't injured in that caraccident.

801
01:17:52,960 --> 01:17:55,590
David.

802
01:17:55,670 --> 01:17:58,220
I've never been injured, Eliijah.

803
01:18:00,550 --> 01:18:02,850
What am I supposed to do?

804
01:18:08,810 --> 01:18:11,650
Go to where people are.

805
01:18:11,770 --> 01:18:14,770
You won't have to look very long.

806
01:18:16,400 --> 01:18:19,320
It's all right to be afraid, David...

807
01:18:19,450 --> 01:18:23,490
because this part won't be
like a comic book.

808
01:18:23,570 --> 01:18:28,450
Real life doesn't fit into little boxes
that were drawn for it.

809
01:19:06,780 --> 01:19:10,710
There's one in the first row.
It's-- It's the second one.

810
01:19:10,830 --> 01:19:13,670
Yes. It's the second one over.

811
01:19:46,870 --> 01:19:48,990
Go back to Africa!

812
01:20:05,340 --> 01:20:07,550
Hey, what's your name?

813
01:20:13,230 --> 01:20:15,440
I think you drank too much.

814
01:21:01,070 --> 01:21:03,110
Can I come in?

815
01:21:03,190 --> 01:21:05,740
Who are you?

816
01:21:05,820 --> 01:21:08,570
I like your house.

817
01:21:08,700 --> 01:21:10,660
Can I come in?

818
01:21:10,780 --> 01:21:12,990
What is this?

819
01:21:14,660 --> 01:21:17,920
No, you can't come in.

820
01:21:18,040 --> 01:21:20,500
Are you sure?

821
01:21:20,580 --> 01:21:22,880
What are-- What are you--

822
01:25:53,070 --> 01:25:55,030
It's okay.

823
01:26:05,410 --> 01:26:07,370
It's okay. It's okay.

824
01:32:51,110 --> 01:32:53,650
I had a bad dream.

825
01:32:59,580 --> 01:33:01,700
It's over now.

826
01:33:29,730 --> 01:33:32,570
I don't know.

827
01:33:32,650 --> 01:33:34,690
I can't believe you'd think that.

828
01:33:34,820 --> 01:33:36,780
I'm just asking you.

829
01:33:40,070 --> 01:33:42,280
I'm making French toast.

830
01:33:57,720 --> 01:34:00,260
I've been thinking about Elijah Price.

831
01:34:01,600 --> 01:34:05,350
If he shows up again, I think
we should call the police, okay?

832
01:34:09,480 --> 01:34:11,440
Okay?

833
01:34:13,980 --> 01:34:15,940
Okay.

834
01:35:24,100 --> 01:35:26,140
You were right.

835
01:36:15,770 --> 01:36:19,820
This is one of Johann Davis'
earliest drawings.

836
01:36:19,940 --> 01:36:22,320
See the villain's eyes?

837
01:36:22,400 --> 01:36:24,610
They're larger than
the other characters'.

838
01:36:24,740 --> 01:36:30,240
They insinuate a slightly skewed
perspective on how they see the world--

839
01:36:31,370 --> 01:36:33,660
just off normal.

840
01:36:33,750 --> 01:36:36,040
He doesn't look scary.

841
01:36:36,170 --> 01:36:38,630
Mm-hmm. That's what I said to my son.

842
01:36:38,750 --> 01:36:41,420
But he says there's always two kinds.

843
01:36:41,510 --> 01:36:45,890
There's the soldier villain
who fights the hero with his hands...

844
01:36:46,010 --> 01:36:50,310
and then there's the real threat--
the brilliant and evil archenemy...

845
01:36:50,390 --> 01:36:52,850
who fights the hero with his mind.

846
01:36:52,980 --> 01:36:54,940
Are you Elijah's mother?

847
01:36:55,060 --> 01:36:58,810
I am. I'm helping him with the sale.

848
01:36:58,900 --> 01:37:01,650
Nice to meet you. I'm David Dunn.

849
01:37:01,780 --> 01:37:03,740
He's spoken ofyou.

850
01:37:03,860 --> 01:37:05,820
Says you're becoming friends.

851
01:37:05,950 --> 01:37:08,320
We are.

852
01:37:08,450 --> 01:37:10,660
Looks like he's doing good today.

853
01:37:11,790 --> 01:37:14,710
I'm very proud of him.

854
01:37:14,790 --> 01:37:17,880
He's come through a lot in his life--

855
01:37:17,960 --> 01:37:21,460
a couple of bad spills
I thought had broken him.

856
01:37:21,590 --> 01:37:24,670
Mm-hmm. They were bad...

857
01:37:25,840 --> 01:37:28,390
but he made it.

858
01:37:28,470 --> 01:37:30,430
Yes, he did.

859
01:37:31,600 --> 01:37:33,810
He's kind of a miracle.

860
01:37:35,980 --> 01:37:37,940
Yes, he is.

861
01:37:41,520 --> 01:37:44,190
- I'll tell him you're here.
- Thank you.

862
01:37:45,530 --> 01:37:49,280
We'll work something out.
Always able to work something out.

863
01:38:14,350 --> 01:38:16,310
It has begun.

864
01:38:19,480 --> 01:38:21,610
Tell me something, David.

865
01:38:22,730 --> 01:38:27,280
When you woke up this morning,
was it still there?

866
01:38:27,360 --> 01:38:30,200
The sadness?

867
01:38:30,320 --> 01:38:32,280
No.

868
01:38:35,910 --> 01:38:38,910
I think this is where we shake hands.

869
01:38:57,980 --> 01:39:00,980
- Look!
- Did you see it?

870
01:39:10,400 --> 01:39:12,870
I worked in that building 25 years.

871
01:39:12,990 --> 01:39:15,120
I know all its secrets.

872
01:39:16,580 --> 01:39:18,540
Secrets?

873
01:39:20,000 --> 01:39:24,880
Like if there ever was a fire
on floors one, two or three...

874
01:39:25,000 --> 01:39:28,510
everyone in that hotel
would be burned alive.

875
01:39:34,470 --> 01:39:37,220
Passengers aren't allowed in there.

876
01:40:20,520 --> 01:40:22,980
Do you know what
the scariest thing is?

877
01:40:26,690 --> 01:40:29,940
To not know your place
in this world...

878
01:40:30,070 --> 01:40:32,610
to not know why you're here.

879
01:40:33,900 --> 01:40:35,870
That's--

880
01:40:37,740 --> 01:40:40,120
That's just an awful feeling.

881
01:40:41,540 --> 01:40:43,830
What have you done?

882
01:40:45,040 --> 01:40:48,040
I almost gave up hope.

883
01:40:48,170 --> 01:40:51,340
There were so many times
I questioned myself.

884
01:40:51,460 --> 01:40:54,010
You killed all those people.

885
01:40:55,300 --> 01:40:58,140
But I found you.

886
01:40:58,220 --> 01:41:01,470
So many sacrifiices...

887
01:41:02,640 --> 01:41:04,600
just to find you.

888
01:41:04,730 --> 01:41:06,690
Jesus Christ!

889
01:41:16,610 --> 01:41:19,370
Now that we know who you are...

890
01:41:20,530 --> 01:41:23,250
I know who I am.

891
01:41:26,830 --> 01:41:29,040
I'm not a mistake.

892
01:41:30,540 --> 01:41:32,670
It all makes sense.

893
01:41:32,800 --> 01:41:37,340
In a comic, you know how you can tell
who the arch-villain's going to be?

894
01:41:37,470 --> 01:41:40,810
He's the exact opposite of the hero.

895
01:41:40,930 --> 01:41:44,680
And most times, they're friends,
like you and me.

896
01:41:44,770 --> 01:41:48,600
I should've known way back when.
You know why, David?

897
01:41:48,690 --> 01:41:50,650
Because of the kids.

898
01:42:00,620 --> 01:42:03,290
They called me Mr. Glass.


